================GIT Init or Push to Existing Repo==============
create a new repository on the command line
echo "# git" >> README.md
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/ngr-ch/git.git
git push -u origin main
…or push an existing repository from the command line
git remote add origin https://github.com/ngr-ch/git.git
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

===============================================================
git config --global -l   # user info
git remote -v            # Remote URL connected
git remote add origin <url>
git remote set-url origin <url>
git config --global user.name “[firstname lastname]”
git config --global user.email “[valid-email]”
git config --global color.ui auto

git init
git pull
git add . or *
git commit -m "commitname"
git status
git branch
git checkout develop

===Revert Commit Locally & Remote Repository===================

If you done multiple commits in locally
git log --oneline
check latest commit id & copy
git reset --hard commit-id or git reset --hard HEAD~1
check git log again

-------------------Remotely Revert Commit----------------------

git log --oneline
check latest commit id & copy
git rever commit-id 
it will ur commit info in vi mode, Simply go to insert mode and type :wq -ENTER
git push -f origin master or develop

